--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TIGER (model code)
  A minimal subset of the TIGER source is vendored under
  python/stemstudio_worker/vendor/tiger/ (the TIGERDNR model and the layers it
  needs at inference time).
  Source:  https://github.com/JusperLee/TIGER
  Author:  Kai Li (李凯)
  License: MIT (see python/stemstudio_worker/vendor/tiger/LICENSE)

TIGER-DnR (model weights)
  The pretrained TIGER-DnR checkpoint is downloaded at runtime from the Hugging
  Face Hub (not distributed with this source).
  Source:  https://huggingface.co/JusperLee/TIGER-DnR
  License: Apache-2.0

demucs (library)
  Research-only MVSEP source can run HTDemucs checkpoints through demucs.
  Public Windows dependency locks do not install it; the existing macOS/Linux
  source environment remains unchanged.
  Source:  https://github.com/adefossez/demucs
  License: MIT

MVSEP-CDX23 (model weights)
  Source for an experimental adapter remains in the repository. Public Windows
  builds do not install, download, or expose this engine or the Max tier because
  the checkpoint repository does not state an adequate model license. Existing
  macOS/Linux behavior is preserved by this port.
  Source:  https://github.com/ZFTurbo/MVSEP-CDX23-Cinematic-Sound-Demixing
  Author:  Roman Solovyev (ZFTurbo)
